<Layout title="Software · Guillermo Parada" prose={true}>
  <h1 class="page-title">Software</h1>
  <p class="page-lead">
    Open-source tools and reproducible workflows that I have developed or contributed to, with a
    focus on alternative splicing analysis, microexon discovery, and RNA regulatory genomics.
  </p>

  <h2>MicroExonator</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>MicroExonator</strong> is a Snakemake-based workflow for the <em>de novo</em> discovery
    and quantification of microexons from RNA-seq data. It was designed to address a common
    limitation of standard RNA-seq pipelines: very short exons are often missed by general-purpose
    splicing workflows. MicroExonator enables systematic microexon discovery and PSI quantification
    across bulk and selected full-length or total-RNA single-cell RNA-seq datasets.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Keywords:</strong> Snakemake, RNA-seq, microexons, alternative splicing, PSI,
    reproducible workflows.
  </p>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/hemberg-lab/MicroExonator" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub repository</a>
    <a class="btn" href="https://doi.org/10.1186/s13059-020-02246-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Genome Biology, 2021</a>
